sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K772008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: GFP - LacZ protein complex with flag tags
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Mustafa Elitok
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This part contains a green fluorescent protein (GFP) as a non-reactive chemical compound (anchor) in order to neutralize the active reactive fixed to it, a reporter device (LacZ enzyme catalyses the reaction of the cleavage of X-Gal which results with blue color change) and a TEV protease cleavage site between them to assemble these two proteins. BBa_772001 and BBa_K772002 are assembled to be used as the trigger of detection in the whole system which ends with the intracellular transfection (or activation) of TEV protease. After the activation, it is planned that TEV protease will cleave this anchor-inducer protein complex to release free the reporter. In conclusion, in this system, the inducer would activate a transcription pathway on the targeted inducible gene or the reporter would indicate that there is a change in the whole system.
This part contains flag tags extra from BBa_K772006 in the GFP region; because it is planned to be used in the Co-IP/SDS-PAGE assay to be isolated.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Cleavage site, LacZ and GFP sequences are gathered from Registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Note that there is an RBS sequence just before the protein sequence in order to eliminate the need of addition of it.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A 3 repeat FLAG (DYKDDDDK) antigen epitope tag used for marking proteins of interest. Proteins carrying this tag can be easily detected using commercial western blotting reagents.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence was designed as part of an oligonucleotide primer on each strand then annealed and ligated into the vector.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TrpZipper2

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: '''TrpZipper''' is a small peptide that folds into a beta-hairpin secondary structure. The indole rings of the Trp form a hydrophobic core. The protein is water soluble and monomer.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Sequence obtained by retro-translation. Codon and mRNA-secondary structure optimized for yeast.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Strep-tag
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a Strep tag tail domain designed to be at the C-terminus of a protein. Strep tags are a type of affinity tag that can be used to purify and/or measure the quantity of proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This domain encodes the Strep tag sequence AWRHPQFGG. The codons at each amino acid position were selected to avoid rare codons as much as possible in organisms like E. coli, humans, mouse, B. subtilis, C. elegans, Streptomyces coelicolor and other common model organisms and/or industrial hosts. Another factor in codon selection was avoiding avoid repeat sequences.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Cloned into pSB1AK3 vector.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Part was constructed by primer annealing.
